5:
Uh... We're getting an awful lot of
stares...
8:
We appear to be almost alien to
them. I suppose running into any
other races is a rarity, aside from
their issues with catfolk.
10:
Perhaps we should be on our way,
especially since we already finished
the job Albert gave us—
13: Where the hell'd you come from?!
19:
What? You telling me I gotta get
permission to enter town or
something? That's the first I've heard
of that.
21:
Giving me attitude? Brave, but
stupid, punk.
24:
Wow, who took a crap in your
breakfast? Oh, wait...
26:
Don't tell me your master told you to
sit, do a trick, and bark before he let
you have food this morning!
29: Oh, now you're asking for it, punk!
32:
The name's Cody, actually. You've
got enough brain cells to remember
that, right?
38:
You really think you're so tough? You
can't even take me without backup.
40:
Small fry are still small fry, even
when there's only three of 'em. I can
take you all with one eye closed—
44:
Tch... Now who said you could invite
more to the party?
49: Jump up and use the wall!
54:
Use the environment to your
advantage! They can't defeat your
mobility!
67: Phew... I think we lost them.
72:
Who are you people? Why'd you get
in my way?
77:
Huh? What do you mean we "got in
your way"?
81:
It seemed like you were in a spot of
trouble. Or were you actually
capable of escaping that situation
on your own?
88:
What even are you? You're no
rabbitfolk. And you can fly? You a
monster or something?
94: I am no monster! I'm the Champion!
97:
The what now? You delusional or
something?
101:
*sigh* In any case, if we
overstepped, then I apologize.
104:
Let's go, Alk. Stella. Albert should
know that a group of dogfolk that
large has come together.
112:
I don't like you. You act like you know
how to fight, even though you can't
fight at all.
114:
Unless you're hiding some sorta
secret power? But you definitely
don't seem like the type to trick your
enemies.
120:
As you can see, I'm smaller than
you. I don't even have the strength
to swing a sword. I am the most
ill-suited for combat out of us all.
124:
Huh? You think you're weak because
you're SMALL? That's a coward's
excuse.
127:
...That's true. I should probably find a
way to be useful in combat, despite
my limitations.
130: Ugh, I REALLY don't like you.
146:
Why? Isn't it obvious? To get
stronger.
148:
That way I can beat the crap outta
any idiots who come barking my
way.
157:
I think I know how to help you with
that.
170:
Huh? What are you, a mercenary
band or something? Well, whatever.
I guess I do owe you one for back
there.
176:
Uh... Was that really such a good
idea?
